obo:GO_0005829  a  owl:Class .

:R-HSA-5689901  a           obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "The JAB1/MPN +/MOV34 (JAMM) domain metalloproteases cleave the isopeptide bond at or near the the attachment point of polyubiquitin and substrate. PSMD14 (RPN11), STAMBP (AMSH), STAMBPL1 (AMSH-LP), and BRCC3 (BRCC36) are highly specific for the K63 poly-Ub linkage, which may be a general characteristic (Eletr & Wilkinson 2014). Two multisubunit complexes represented elsewhere in Reactome contain JAMM DUBs. The proteasome 19S lid complex includes PSMD14, an endopeptidase that cleaves poly-Ub chains from substrates as they are degraded by the proteasome (Verma et al. 2002). The COP9-Signalosome contains COPS5 (CSN5), which deconjugates the Ub-like modifier Nedd8, modulating the activity of the SCF E3 ligase (Cope et al. 2002). <br><br>JAMM DUB catalysis requires nucleophilic attack on the carbonyl carbon of the isopeptide bond by an activated water molecule bound to Zn2+ and a conserved glutamate. A negatively-charged tetrahedral transition state ensues, and a nearby conserved Ser/Thr in the JAMM domains stabilizes the oxyanion. The tetrahedral intermediate then collapses and the Glu serves as a general base donating a proton to the leaving Lys side chain (Ambroggio et al. 2004)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Metalloprotease DUBs" ;
        dc:contributor      "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Edited: Jupe, Steve, 2016-05-05" , "Authored: Jupe, Steve, 2015-04-16" , "Reviewed: Meldal, Birgit, 2016-05-16" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-5689901" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-5688426/R-HSA-5688426> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

